d on master columns (`PoTableColumn[]`), not on detail columns."],[1938,"**Root cause:** po-table adds an internal selectable-column (`po-table-column-selectable`)\nof **56px** that is NOT represented in `PoTableColumn[]`. This hidden 56px is added on\ntop of the sum of all `p-width` values, pushing the table wider than its container."],[1976,"**Root cause:** po-table adds the row to its internal `selectedRows` array **before**\ndispatching the `(p-selected)` event. Any synchronous `$selected: false` change on the\nitems signal is processed in the same change-detection cycle — but po-table's internal\nstate already has the row, so the visual state stays selected even though the data says\n`$selected: false`. This desync causes a second `(p-selected)` on the next click instead\nof `(p-unselected)`."],[1966,"**Root cause:** The correct Angular input alias is `p-maxlength` (no hyphen between `max` and `length`)."],[2007,"**Rule:** Every `po-table` generated in a `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` component MUST\nhave `[p-height]` set. No exceptions. A table inside an `@if` block is especially vulnerable."],[628,"**Seletor:** `po-page-dynamic-detail`\\\n&#x2A;*Pacote:** `@po-ui/ng-templates`"],[608,"**Seletor:** `po-page-dynamic-edit`\\\n&#x2A;*Pacote:** `@po-ui/ng-templates`"],[576,"**Seletor:** `po-page-dynamic-search`\\\n&#x2A;*Pacote:** `@po-ui/ng-templates`"],[552,"**Seletor:** `po-page-dynamic-table`"],[244,"**Sem `any`**"],[2090,"**Sempre** usar no submit — não omite campos desabilitados"],[242,"**Signals**"],[238,"**Standalone**"],[1940,"**Step 1 — Reduce the internal checkbox column via `::ng-deep`:**"],[1941,"**Step 2 — Calculate `p-width` values so that their sum + checkbox = panel width:**"],[1942,"**Step 3 — Use gap: 4px (not 8px) between panels** to maximize panel width:"],[1992,"**Symptom:** `po-table` renders correctly in the DOM but is invisible when the page is first\nnavigated to. It only becomes visible after the user moves the mouse or triggers any event.\nThe bug is most noticeable when the table is inside an `@if` block."],[1965,"**Symptom:** Angular compilation error: `NG8002: Can't bind to 'p-max-length' since it isn't a known property of 'po-input'`."],[2008,"**Symptom:** Binding `(p-value-change)=\"myHandler($event)\"` on `po-dynamic-form` compiles\nwithout errors but the handler is never called, regardless of what the user types."],[1933,"**Symptom:** Buttons placed in the same flex row as `po-input` fields appear 8px lower\nthan the visible input field edge, even with `align-items: flex-end` on the container."],[1970,"**Symptom:** No TypeScript error but the selection never fires / rows never accumulate."],[1928,"**Symptom:** Page renders the title/header but ALL content below it is invisible on first\nload (filter bar, tables, buttons — everything inside `ng-content`)."],[1989,"**Symptom:** TypeScript compiler throws `TS2353: Object literal may only specify known properties, and 'width' does not exist in type 'PoTableDetailColumn'` when defining columns inside `buildDetailConfig()`."],[1975,"**Symptom:** When `(p-selected)` fires and you want to reject the selection (e.g., guard\nvalidation failed), setting `$selected: false` on the item synchronously has no effect.\nThe row stays visually selected, and clicking it again fires `(p-selected)` instead of\n`(p-unselected)`, so the warning message fires a second time."],[1937,"**Symptom:** When two `po-table` components are placed side by side (flex:1 each),\neach table generates a horizontal scrollbar even though the specified `p-width` values\nseem reasonable."],[2000,"**Synchronous** — runs inside `ngDoCheck`, same CD cycle"],[972,"**Tabelas**"],[56,"**Templates**"],[2516,"**Todos os endpoints de escrita (POST, PUT, DELETE) devem retornar este formato\nem caso de erro (4xx/5xx).**"],[2394,"**Total**"],[215,"**Use `(req)` apenas em campos realmente obrigatórios no formulário:**"],[986,"**Utilitários**"],[392,"**Verificação de build** — compila automaticam